1. Define the composite mapping:
$$f_0(x)=\frac{x}{a},\quad f_1(x)=\frac{x+b}{a},$$
so
$$f(x)\;=\;(f_1\circ f_0)(x)
\;=\;f_1\!\Bigl(\frac{x}{a}\Bigr)
\;=\;\frac{\frac{x}{a}+b}{a}
\;=\;\frac{x}{a^2}+\frac{b}{a}.$$

2. For the nested intervals $K_{n+1}=f(K_n)$ whose lengths tend to zero, the unique point in the intersection satisfies the fixed-point equation
$$x=f(x).$$

3. Substitute $a=3$ and $b=2$ into $f(x)$:
$$f(x)=\frac{x}{3^2}+\frac{2}{3}
=\frac{x}{9}+\frac{2}{3}.$$

4. Solve the fixed-point equation:
$$x=\frac{x}{9}+\frac{2}{3}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
x-\frac{x}{9}=\frac{2}{3}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
\frac{8}{9}x=\frac{2}{3}
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
x=\frac{2}{3}\cdot\frac{9}{8}
=\frac{18}{24}
=\frac{3}{4}.$$
